  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Elephants responses to the resumption of hunting</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Botswana, hunting of elephants has been reintroduced to address human-elephant conflict (HEC)  and to bring income to rural areas. However, there is uncertainty how hunting may affect daily life&apos;s. Elephants who have experienced a hunt are likely to become more aggressive, which could lead to further increases, not decreases, of HEC in rural communities. Understanding behavioural changes of elephants towards humans after the resumption of hunting is important to avoid an escalation in HEC.</narrative>
  </description>
